          "text": "![State-of-the-art web search API](https://exa.imgix.net/simpleqa-eval-7.png?fm=avif&q=50)",
          "charCount": 90
        },
        {
          "text": "- For **Exa**, we use simple, prompted off-the-shelf LLMs -- gemini-1.5-flash to generate the search query, and 4o-mini to generate the answer from the results.\n- For **Bing**, we pass the SimpleQA query and use 4o-mini with the same prompt to summarize.\n- For **Perplexity**, we use Sonar-Pro, their flagship API for web RAG. We pass the SimpleQA query directly to Perplexity.\n- We use **GPT-4o** as a baseline without web access, scoring the output given the prompt as in the original SimpleQA benchmark.",
          "charCount": 506
        },
        {
          "text": "[MSMARCO](https://microsoft.github.io/msmarco/) is a canonical query and labelled document dataset in information retrieval (IR) based on Bing searches. Typically, MSMARCO is used to benchmark IR system retrieval over the MSMARCO document index. However, in order to compare to public providers with varying indexes, we couldn't rely on the labelled documents, and instead use an LLM-as-Judge to evaluate the results returned from each search engine directly. While this approach is necessarily approximate, LLM grades in IR are [found to](https://arxiv.org/html/2405.04727v1) have high correlation with human grades.",
          "charCount": 617
        }
